{
  "version": 1,
  "updated_at": "2026-05-16T19:08:51.477659",
  "rules": [
    "[P1] Prioritize state-alignment constraints (cardinality limits) over clinical preference.",
    "[P1] Validate resource IDs and perform definitive counts before execution.",
    "[P1] Separate verification findings from action execution.",
    "[P1] Do not conclude a task until system state change is confirmed.",
    "[P1] Explicitly cite search parameters, date ranges, and audit trails for 'no data' conclusions, distinguishing between 'not found' vs 'out of timeframe'.",
    "[P1] Normalize date formats and calculate duration against timestamps.",
    "[P1] Perform a final cross-check of record counts and environment state consistency.",
    "[P1] Prioritize order reconciliation: modify/replace existing before initiating new.",
    "[P1] Categorize data absence (e.g., 'never recorded' vs 'outdated') to inform logic.",
    "[P1] Distinguish between distinct clinical categories (e.g., diagnostic vs. immunization) when verifying historical procedures.",
    "[P1] Do not execute preemptive actions unless explicitly instructed to override conditions.",
    "[P1] Explicitly map identified orders to clinical intent before modification.",
    "[P1] Explicitly state decision logic (e.g., 'Threshold not met, terminating') before any state-changing action.",
    "[P1] Explicitly state the date of the most recent relevant record to justify new order necessity.",
    "[P1] Map required clinical indications to order requests when existing data is insufficient.",
    "[P1] Perform exhaustive search across all relevant entity codes and broader category levels before declaring absence of historical data.",
    "[P1] Query system metadata/timestamps to establish reference dates for relative temporal calculations.",
    "[P1] Strictly enforce conditional logic: only execute secondary tasks if primary trigger criteria are fully satisfied.",
    "[P1] Terminate workflows immediately when missing primary data prevents conditional logic.",
    "[P1] Translate state discrepancies directly into executable commands.",
    "[P1] Use standardized terminology (LOINC, SNOMED) and synonymous clinical abbreviations for data queries.",
    "[P1] Verify antecedent conditions, active orders, and counter-orders before acting.",
    "[P1] Utilize server-side search parameters to filter data at the source.",
    "[P1] Decompose requests into sequential steps: fetch, filter, and aggregate.",
    "[P1] Define search timeframe, scope, and entity identifiers before querying."
  ],
